headline: Kohl's names Michaels CEO Ashley Buchanan to assume top job, effective Jan. 15
summary: Department store retailer Kohl's Inc. says Michaels CEO and retail veteran Ashley Buchanan will take over its top job, effective January 15.  Buchanan succeeds Tom Kingsbury, who will stay as an adviser to the new CEO and retain his position on Kohl’s board until his retirement in May 2025.  Kingsbury served as Kohl's interim CEO in December 2022 and was named its permanent leader in February 2023.

headline: Walmart CFO Says They Don't Want To Raise Prices, But 'Prices Will Go Up For Consumers' Due To Upcoming Tariffs
summary: Walmart’s CFO, John David Rainey, recently said that if President-elect Donald Trump's proposed tariffs take effect, Walmart (NYSE:WMT) will need to raise prices on certain items. Speaking with CNBC, Rainey explained, "We never want to raise prices. Our model is everyday low prices. But there probably will be cases where prices will go up for consumers." headline: Amazon Black Friday Gets Early Start. Why E-Commerce Could Outpace Total Holiday Spending Growth..
